In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 2009 as National Wilderness Month in the United States. He highlights the importance of the American wilderness as an irreplaceable part of the nation's heritage and emphasizes the need to preserve it for future generations. The article mentions the Wilderness Act, which was signed by President Lyndon B. Johnson 45 years ago, and the National Wilderness Preservation System it established. Obama acknowledges the bipartisan support for wilderness protection and highlights his administration's commitment to protecting the country's wilderness heritage. He also encourages Americans to visit and enjoy wilderness areas, learn more about their heritage, and take action to protect and preserve these national treasures.